To install the WPF Splash Screen Item Templates for Visual Studio 2008 Sp1:

* Make sure that you have  Visual Studio 2008 Sp1 and make sure  it is closed.
* Launch SplashScreenTemplateSetup.msi
* You are done:
     - In Visual Studio you can now Right-Click on your Project and then click “Add / New Item… / Splash Screen (WPF)”. 
     - Compile and run.
     - You should see the default Splash Screen image showing. You likely want to modify our default Splash Screen image. 
* For additional info see : http://blogs.msdn.com/jgoldb/archive/2008/08/12/what-s-new-in-wpf-3-5-sp1-splash-screen-to-improve-perceived-startup-perf.aspx 

